sists play an extremely important role in your ability to function and contribute to events.  Someone that continually takes damage from area effect spells because their resists are low is far more of a liability than they are a help.  Thus, there are minimum requirements for resist gear before joining the guild.  The following stats are the minimums of any given UNBUFFED character.  Songs, spells, potions, or items that cast resist spells do NOT count towards your total.  There are 3 separate requirements at the moment, all which can be achieved using 3 separate sets of gear if necessary.  You may sacrifice your character's main stats (int, wis, etc.) in order to reach these.<br><br>1) 100 Magic, 100 Fire, 100 cold SIMULTANEOUSLY<br>2) 100 Magic, 100 Poison SIMULTANEOUSLY<br>3) 100 Magic, 100 Disease SIMULTANEOUSLY<br><br><br>Item Checklist<br>------------------------<br>There are several items which come in very handy during events.  We feel several of these items are a necessity, and have made them a requirement:<br><br>Permanant Enduring Breath item - Songs, spells, or items with a casting time do NOT count.  You need an item that is either a permanant effect, or instant-cast enduring breath.<br><br>Journeymans Boots - An independent form transportation is often necessary for our members to reach various locations during events.  These also serve as a secondary right-click item for outdoor zones.  Traveler's boots ARE acceptable as well, however, SoW potions are NOT.<br><br>Right click instant-buff item - We require that you have at least one item that is a self-only instant cast buff.  The item MUST BE INDOOR USABLE.  Journeymans boots and items with charges do NOT count.  Suggestions are Velium Coldain Ring (preferred), Shrunken Goblin Skull earring.  Melee classes should seek to acquire both (however it is not a requirement.)<br><br><br>Key Checklist<br>------------------------<br>Many zones that we visit require a key to access.  Everyone should have these keys on hand at any time for events.  The keys you are REQUIRED to have are as follows:<br><br>Sebilis Key<br>Charisis Key (howling stones)<br>Tooth of the Cobalt Scar<br>Shrine Key (key to exit skyshrine)<br><br>It would also look favorably upon you if you had some of your veeshan's peak key quest completed.  Many of these parts are quite simple and can be done alone.  A good guide can be found here:<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/mct_02/vpkey.html">www.geocities.com/mct_02/vpkey.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><br>------------------------<br><br>Having completed these requirements you will be well on your way to becoming a member of Ascending Dawn.  If there are any ambiguities/questions about the checklist, you may post here or contact us in game for clarification.<br><br>Thank you for your interest. <p>--<br><br><img src=http://wsmake.org/~nc/praxx.jpg><br><br>"...It is simple common sense then, that the taller a being is, the farther his mind and heart are from the truth.  Always be wary of those larger in stature than us." - Grand Historian Thoridain</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/upraxxrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PraxxRZ</A> at: 11/9/01 3:58:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/unietche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nietche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/10/01 1:08:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ATTENTION Potential Recruits</span><hr size=1> C 'ya in a year.<br><br>Nietche <p>"Sometimes killing is the greatest of charity.""War is necessary. Peace is never eternal.""Contention is part law, part 